column1: ! List the wires you want the wiring operator to skip

column2: all lines and nodes will be made lower case.
all white space will be removed.

column3: to pin/brc entry can be in any order.

column1: ! The following can go in To or From:
! The wildcard '*' matches all pins and transfers
! Do not place a wildcard in the from and to column.
! A pin at a node. e.g. 'pin{+5V}' or 'pin{1%TDI}'
! A pin at a node for any board number;
! A pin at a node across a range of board numbers
! A Transfer at a node. e.g. 'T{+5V}' or 'T{1%TDI}'
! A Transfer at a node for any board number;
! A Transfer at a node across a range of board numbers
! The following can go in To only.:
! A Probe at a node. e.g. 'P{+5V}' or 'P{1%TDI}'
! A Probe at a node for any board number;
! A Probe at a node across a range of board numbers
! If the wire to be removed cannot be found in the wires file
! The program will report an error.
